Letting $y = \frac{p(x)}{q(x)}$:
\begin{align*}
y &= \frac{(x + c)(x - 4)}{(x - 2)^2} \qquad \text{for some constant } c \\
&= \frac{x^2 + (c-4)x - 4c}{x^2 - 4x + 4} \\
&= \frac{-(x^2 - (4-c)x - 4c)}{(x - 2)^2} \\
&= \frac{(x - 2)(c - x - 4)}{(x - 2)^2} \\
&= \frac{c - x - 4}{x - 2}
